{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.6",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 6 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:1",
      "text": "But Job answered, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:2",
      "text": "O that my sins, whereby I have deserved wrath, and the calamity that I suffer, were weighed in a balance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:3",
      "text": "As the sand of the sea, this would appear heavier: therefore, my words are full of sorrow:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:4",
      "text": "For the arrows of the Lord are in me, the rage whereof drinketh up my spirit, and the terrors of the Lord war against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:5",
      "text": "Will the wild ass bray when he hath grass? or will the ox low when he standeth before a full manger?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:6",
      "text": "Or can an unsavoury thing be eaten, that is not seasoned with salt? or can a man taste that which, when tasted, bringeth death?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:7",
      "text": "The things which before my soul would not touch, now, through anguish, are my meats.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:8",
      "text": "Who will grant that my request may come: and that God may give me what I look for?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:9",
      "text": "And that he that hath begun may destroy me, that he may let loose his hand, and cut me off?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:10",
      "text": "And that this may be my comfort, that afflicting me with sorrow, he spare not, nor I contradict the words of the Holy one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:11",
      "text": "For what is my strength, that I can hold out? or what is my end, that I should keep patience?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:12",
      "text": "My strength is not the strength of stones, nor is my flesh of brass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:13",
      "text": "Behold there is no help for me in myself, and my familiar friends also are departed from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:14",
      "text": "He that taketh away mercy from his friend, forsaketh the fear of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:15",
      "text": "My brethren have passed by me, as the torrent that passeth swiftly in the valleys.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:16",
      "text": "They that fear the hoary frost, the snow shall fall upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:17",
      "text": "At the time when they shall be scattered they shall perish: and after it groweth hot, they shall be melted out of their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:18",
      "text": "The paths of their steps are entangled: they shall walk in vain, and shall perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:19",
      "text": "Consider the paths of Thema, the ways of Saba, and wait a little while.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:20",
      "text": "They are confounded, because I have hoped: they are come also even unto me, and are covered with shame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:21",
      "text": "Now you are come: and now, seeing my affliction, you are afraid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:22",
      "text": "Did I say: Bring to me, and give me of your substance?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:23",
      "text": "Or deliver me from the hand of the enemy, and rescue me out of the hand of the mighty?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:24",
      "text": "Teach me, and I will hold my peace: and if I have been ignorant of any thing, instruct me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:25",
      "text": "Why have you detracted the words of truth, whereas there is none of you that can reprove me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:26",
      "text": "You dress up speeches only to rebuke, and you utter words to the wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:27",
      "text": "You rush in upon the fatherless, and you endeavour to overthrow your friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:28",
      "text": "However, finish what you have begun: give ear and see whether I lie.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:29",
      "text": "Answer, I beseech you, without contention: and speaking that which is just, judge ye.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.6.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:30",
      "text": "And you shall not find iniquity in my tongue, neither shall folly sound in my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
